This paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it presents an implementation of a probabilistic first-order logic that can be integrated with deep learning infrastructure. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of neural networks for differentiable functions. Additionally, it could belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as it deals with knowledge-base triples. It could also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves logical reasoning. Finally, it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it involves the use of neural networks.
